item.description:
Shifting a float by 1 approximately squares or square-roots it very quickly. This is probably useful for RMS error calculation or getting the length of a vector.

```
static float garbage_len(float a, float b){
  return utf(ftu(
      utf(ftu(a)<<1u)
      +utf(ftu(b)<<1u)
  )>>1u);
}
```
